column1: Fluorescence - Transmissivity - PAR are nominal and unedited except that some records were removed in editing temperature and salinity.
The Oxygen:Dissolved:CTD data should be considered:
• ± 0.4 ml/l from 200 to 400 dbar; values tend to be somewhat high in this high gradient region.
• data below 500 dbar tend to be low.
• data below 1000 dbar are considered unreliable by the manufacturer.
For details on the processing see processing report: 2007-15-proc.pdf
